And when we got there,
we realized the

00:11:03.110 --> 00:11:04.390
ground was way too soft.

00:11:04.390 --> 00:11:08.550
The cameras wouldn't be, like,
they wouldn't stay sturdy.

00:11:08.550 --> 00:11:10.020
Like, we were going to hardware
stores, trying to

00:11:10.020 --> 00:11:12.970
find lumber so that we could
build a bracket that could be

00:11:12.970 --> 00:11:14.280
mounted to the wall.

00:11:14.280 --> 00:11:15.030
And you couldn't find

00:11:15.030 --> 00:11:16.520
pressure-treated lumber in Iceland.

00:11:16.520 --> 00:11:19.030
And then everything was metric
units, and all of our tools

00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:19.880
didn't work.

00:11:19.880 --> 00:11:23.920
It was just all these seemingly
small, easy, little,

00:11:23.920 --> 00:11:27.030
minuscule details were really
putting the whole project into

00:11:27.030 --> 00:11:31.490
jeopardy from the very, very
first installation in Iceland.

